Hundreds of residents of Share/Oke-Ode communities of Ifelodun Local Government Area of Kwara State were at the weekend empowered with items worth millions of naira to address unemployment and poverty. Thee lawmaker representing the constituency in the Kwara State House of Assembly, Hon Razaq Owolabi who explained that he had to take a bank loan to put smiles on the faces of his constituents, presented six cars, 43 sewing machines, 20 sprayers, deep freezers, generators, clippers and 5000 exercise books for primary and secondary school students across the 10 wards that constitute the constituency. 